data.name: tut18k.ToolTip
data.value:
Not a real Hitchance but works like it...
100 = 100% = It only shoots if the chance is 100% to hit the Enemy (Probably won't shoot at all, the chance that it will 100% hit is low)
10 = 10% = It shoots if the chance to hit the Enemy is 10 or higher (Will shoot fast and miss shots)
70-90 is optimal

data.name: tut16b.ToolTip
data.value:
Imagine a square that lies around your Enemy. You can enlarge this square with the "Pixel X" function to up and down.
As soon as your crosshair reaches this square, the conditions for "Aimbot-Target" will take effect. That means your Aimbot Smoothnes will be switch from the "Aimbot-Searching" to the "Aimbot-Target". (Also your "Delay" will activate as soon as you reach that Square)
Use this if you want to be able to move your crosshair freely on the Enemy as soon as you reach the opponent or this square with your crosshair.

data.name: tut17b.ToolTip
data.value:
If you want to disable your Aimbot while you are aiming at your target you can set a delay. For example if you put in 1000 = 1000ms = 1second it will disable the aimbot for 1 second if you aim at your target. Use this if the Aimbot is too sticky for you.
Lower Values are more legit.

data.name: tutt1.Text
data.value:
About Aimbot:
This feature "Aimbot" automatically aims at your Enemy if you look in their direction. If you enabled it you have to choose a Keybind. If you press and hold that Key your Aimbot will lock onto your enemy.
You can find the Keybind at the Bottom of this Program. Just scroll down later and you will find it.

data.name: intro1.Text
data.value:
Welcome User to iBaseult. If you need help or have questions about the Cheat please do the short Tutorial!
Recode by Baseult - Credits to bluefire1337 for the original base source - Credits to Grizzly22 for the input injector method

data.name: tutt2.Text
data.value:
About Ragebot:
"Ragebot" is almost like Aimbot but with an additional feature named "Triggerbot".
It automatically Aims at your Enemy and also automatically shoots as soon as your crosshair is over your Enemy.
It also uses the Keybind Ragebot. Press and Hold that Keybind to use Ragebot after you enabled it with the Checkbox

data.name: Introt.Text
data.value:
About Configs:
First of all, asking me or anyone else about a "Perfect OP Config" will not work.
All Settings are related to your Screen Resolution, Monitor Refreshrate and Ingame Mouse Sensitivity.
You may copy my or anyone else configs but they probably will work different for you as for them.
Please take yourself 5 minutes to test around and make your own config instead of spamming others.

data.name: tutt3.Text
data.value:
About Triggerbot:
"Triggerbot" automatically shoots as soon as your crosshair is over your Enemy.
It uses a keybind Triggerbot. Press and Hold that Keybind to use Triggerbot after you enabled it with the Checkbox

data.name: tutt10.Text
data.value:
About Humanizer:
"Humanizer" is the Speed of your Aimbot. It defines how fast your Aimbot will Aim at your Enemy.
If your Aimbot shakes or flicks and aims around that means your value is too high. Decrease it then!

data.name: tutt11.Text
data.value:
About Fov X / Y:
"Fov" is Field of View, the Area around your Crosshair in which the Feature is Active.
You have to set your crosshair near the enemy until your Fov is on your Enemy, then the Feature will activate.
If you increase that Value it increase your Field of View so your Feature will work even if you don't look near your Enemy.

data.name: tutt12.Text
data.value:
About Aimoffset:
Aimoffset is your Aimposition. If you have it at 0-25 it will Aim at the Enemy head. Any higher Value will Aim lower at the Enemies Body.
Higher Numbers = Aims lower at enemy body Lower / Negative Numbers = Aims higher at enemy head

data.name: tutt13.Text
data.value:
About Aimbot - Target:
"Aimbot - Targets" Settings are active as soon as you reach the Enemy with your Crosshair.
All Settings from "Aimbot - Searching" will be overwritten until you leave the Enemy with your Crosshair.
Use this if you want to set another Aimbot Speed as soon as you reach your Enemy so you are able to still move your Crosshair.
BE AWARE THAT USING FEATURES IN "AIMBOT - TARGET" MIGHT SLOW DOWN THE AIMBOT!

data.name: tutt14.Text
data.value:
About Aimbot - Target - Enable / Disable:
If you don't want a different Aimspeed if you aim at your Enemy just leave that Checkbox unticked.
Otherwise you can enable it so all Settings will take effect.
BE AWARE THAT USING AIMBOT - TARGET MIGHT SLOW DOWN THE AIMBOT!

data.name: tutt15.Text
data.value:
About Pixel Fov X/Y:
This is the Area around your Enemy in which your Aimbot Target Settings will activate.
It is like a second inner foc of your Enemy. As soon as you reach that Area it will change form Aimbot - Searching to Aimbot - Target Settings!

data.name: tutt18.Text
data.value:
About Hitchance:
Hitchance calculates your chance to hit the target you are currently aiming at, and only shoot if it's above the limit.
As described before, Ragebot will Aim at your Target and autoshoot as soon as your Crosshair reaches the enemy.
If you set the hitchance to 90 the chance to hit your Target has to be 90% or higher or it won't autoshoot.
(No this is actually not a real Hitchance but it works like one)

data.name: tutt19.Text
data.value:
About Firerate:
As described your Ragebot will shoot automatically. You can change the shootspeed (how often it shoots in a minute)
If you want it to shoot slower, decrease the value, else increase the value it is basically a delay between your shoots

data.name: tutt20.Text
data.value:
About NoRecoil:
You can adjust your NoRecoil. The NoRecoil Standalone is active if you shoot manual with your mouse.
The NoRecoil Aimbot is active if your Triggerbot or Ragebot automatically shoots at your Enemy
Default for Standalone is 0 (you can make it more or less norecoil). for Aimbot use smth around 1-10.

data.name: tutt21.Text
data.value:
About Keybinds:
You have Keybinds for Aimbot, Ragebot and Triggerbot.
If you activate "AimKey" you will have to use these Keybinds, otherwise these Features are allways active.
If you activate "Hold" you have to Hold the Key to activate the Feature, otherwise it is toggle on / off.
